transportation most products were sold to industrial manufacturing customers for use as additives ingredients or intermediates that add value to their end products additionally the company considered itself a strong competitor in the global market based on its ranking of its products within given sectors as defined by sector industries and operating segments business segmentsedit the company had two reporting segments industrial performance products including the petroleum additives and urethanes businesses industrial engineered products comprised the great lakes solutions and organometallic specialties businesses industrial performance productsedit this segment markets synthetic lubricants and greases synthetic basestocks lubricant additives and urethanes industrial engineered productsedit this segment marketed brominated performance products flame retardants fumigants and organometallics locations and facilitiesedit the company had plants in  countries in locations such as connecticut new jersey arkansas germany italy china taiwan mexico brazil and the united kingdom on april   the companys locations were acquired by lanxess legaledit firemaster  is one of chemturas brominated flame retardants it is marketed as a flammabilitydecreasing additive for polyurethane foam used in upholstered furniture as polyurethane foam ages and breaks down into fine dust additives like firemaster  can leach out and be absorbed inhaled or ingested in a  investigative series the chicago tribune reported that a team of researchers detected harmful effects from firemaster  at levels that were significantly lower than those used in the studies conducted on behalf of chemtura in response to the studies linking flame retardants to accumulation in humans and resulting potential harm california governor jerry brown proposed a regulation phasing out flameretardant chemicals in furniture on january   chemtura filed a lawsuit in sacramento county superior court attempting to force the state of california to leave the old standards in place in that lawsuit the company alleges that chemtura would be irreparably harmed if the proposed new regulation were not rescinded in november  governor browns office announced publication of the new flammability standards with mandatory compliance scheduled to begin on january   in midjanuary  chemtura filed a lawsuit against the state of california alleging the california bureau of electronics and appliance repair home furnishings and thermal insulation failed to comply with its legislative mandate by issuing a revised fire safety standard that does not address the risk of ignition from open flame ignition sources on september   california governor jerry brown signed a bill requiring upholstered furniture labeling indicate whether the product contains toxic flameretardant chemicals this labelling requirement has triggered demand for furniture free of flame retardants see alsoedit philadelphia portal list of companies based in the philadelphia area list of chemical companies list of largest chemical producers referencesedit  a b c d e f chemtura corporation files form k globenewswire  chemtura february   retrieved    chemtura reports fourth quarter  financial results nasdaq february   retrieved    a b c d chemtura corp  form k  ex  exhibit   february   getfilingscom february   retrieved    a b about chemtura chemturacom  retrieved    a b rudnick leslie r  lubricant additives chemistry and applications second edition crc press taylor  francis pp    timeline  isbn    a b c plunkett jack w july  plunketts chemicals coatings  plastics industry almanac  houston texas plunkett research limited isbn    a b c d  this article incorporates public domain material from websites or documents of the united states government form k online  pdf for the fiscal year ended december   us securities and exchange commission  february  retrieved  may    company  people wall street journal dow jones  company inc retrieved  june    financials wall